Class AbstractJavaSourceGenerator

java.lang.Object
  com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.backend.AbstractJavaSourceGenerator
Direct Known Subclasses:
JUnitConverter, JUnitConverter.JUnitGeneratorWorker
public abstract class AbstractJavaSourceGenerator
extends java.lang.Object

Base class for KeYTestGen backend modules generating Java code for various test frameworks. Provides essential utility methods and formatting constants.

writeClassHeader

protected void writeClassHeader(java.lang.String[] annotations,
                                java.lang.String visibility,
                                java.lang.String modifier,
                                java.lang.String name)
Writes the signature head of a Java class declaration with the canonical form: 

 [@annotation]
 [access] [modifiers] Type Name([parameters])

where [@annotation] is empty, or a set of valid Java annotations.

where [access] is empty, or exactly one of the following: 

 public, protected, private

where [modifier] is empty, or a set containing at most 1 of the following: 

 final, abstract

Declaring a method opens a new scope, and hence increases the indentation level for the text.

Parameters:
visibility - the [access] for the class
modifier - the [modifiers] for the class
name - the Name for the class

writeMethodHeader

protected void writeMethodHeader(java.lang.String[] annotations,
                                 java.lang.String visibility,
                                 java.lang.String[] modifiers,
                                 java.lang.String returnType,
                                 java.lang.String name,
                                 java.lang.String[] parameters,
                                 java.lang.String[] exceptions)
Writes the signature head of a Java method declaration with the canonical form: 

 [@annotation]
 [access] [modifiers] Type Name([parameters])

where [@annotation] is empty, or a set of valid Java annotations.

where [access] is empty, or exactly one of the following: 

 public, protected, private

where [modifier] is empty, or a set containing at most 1 of each of the following: 

 static, final, native, abstract

where Type is a reference or primitive Java type, Name is a legitimate Java identifier, and where [parameters] is either empty, or a set of bounded size consisting of elements with the following form: 

 [modifier] Type Name

Where [modifier] is either empty or the element final, Type is a valid Java type, and Name is a valid Java identifier.

Declaring a method opens a new scope, and hence increases the indentation level for the text.

Parameters:
annotations - the [annotations] for the method
visibility - the [access] for the method
returnType - the Type for the method
modifiers - the [modifiers] for the method
name - the Name for the method
